item.title: How make client unleachable
item.dc:creator: @Sanskrit Sanskrit
item.description:
@Sanskrit wrote:

Firstly, delete all of the java files within the client so that they would have to decompile each one to get at the java coding. You could also rename the class files after that, but I think you would have to rename the imports as well. Then, you could make it even harder to leech by creating a manifest file and jarring the client, then they would have to extract all of the class files with WinRar. Unfortunately, they can get into the cache no matter what.
